SUMMARY:25 Years Of Eskimo Recordings (Nadiem Shah)
LOCATION:The Floor
DESCRIPTION:Best Kept Secret 2026 test import - shifted 1 day earlier\nStage: The Floor\nTime: Saturday 13 June
  2026 19:30 - Saturday 13 June 2026 20:30\n\nNadiem Shah playing an infect
 ious selection of the influential label from Ghent\n\nThe promised landers
  have their DFA label. The low landers have Eskimo Recordings.\nThis highl
 y influential label from Belgium is as much known for its artists (Aeropla
 ne\, Prins Thomas\, Aili) as it is for its compilations. It all started wi
 th the eclectic parties that took place during the late nineties in the Es
 kimo Fabriek in Ghent. These underground parties got famous for mixing new
  wave\, acid\, funk and rock ‘n’ roll\, introducing local DJs such as 
 The Glimmers and The Flying Dewaele Brothers. At The Floor label manager N
 adiem Shah will takes us through 25 years of leftfield clubbing. Cooler th
 an being cool. Eskimo!\n\nArtist source: https://www.bestkeptsecret.nl/ban
 ds/25-years-of-eskimo-recordings-nadiem-shah\nSchedule source: https://www
 .bestkeptsecret.nl/program/saturday/schedule
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
